Title: The phase free, longitudinal, magnetic component of vacuum

electromagnetismAuthors: A. E. Chubykalo, M. W. Evans and R. Smirnov-Rueda

Comments: ReVTeX file, 7pp., no figures

Journal-ref: Found.Phys.Lett. 10 (1997) 93

A charge $q$ moving in a reference laboratory system with constant velocity{\bf V} in the $X$-axis produces in the $Z$-axis a longitudinal, phase free,vacuum magnetic field which is identified as the radiated ${\bf B}^{(3)}$ fieldof Evans, Vigier and others.